- scan_sequences() OOM crash with many motifs and large sequences: the C++ scan
  kernel (src/scan_sequences.cpp, scan_single_seq/scan_single_seq_NA) builds a full
  O(nmotifs x nseqs x seqlen) integer-score grid in memory before format_results()
  applies the threshold filter. For 100 motifs x athaliana-sized input this is ~13 GB
  resident before any filtering. Fix: merge score-emission and threshold filter into
  a streaming hit-emitter so only hits above threshold are kept; restructure
  format_results() accordingly. See scan_sequences.cpp lines 41-79 and 123-173.
